metadata.name: Ailerons #48
metadata.description:
Ailerons, littering the factory floor, custom made and ready to be fitted to their respective aircraft. An accent trickles across the canvas, coloring any object in its path.

A study of light, built entirely in a 2d renderer, creating light and shadow with math and logic.

Press 's' to save a .png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: Business District #13
metadata.description:
The business district is bustling with activity. Skyscrapers tower above and modern buildings line the streets. Trees provide shade and beauty in the walkways. This is a place where people come to work and to shop. There is a feeling of excitement in the air.
Three modes. Many aspect ratios.
- press 's' to save in .svg
- press 'p' to save in .png

metadata.name: broken laser printer #100
metadata.description:
If I have a super-power, it is this. When I get to within one meter of a printer or photocopier, they malfunction. Sometimes they jam, sometimes the sheets of paper get crumpled and torn, and other times the toner cartridges and drums get fouled and streaked.

This artwork is an abstract depiction of the state of printouts under the influence of my superpower. I always try to use my powers for good, but I am only human, and the result often has unintended side-effects.

Press "s" to save image.

Press "q" if you want to relieve stress caused by malfunctioning printers (does not affect the artwork in any way).

metadata.name: Indistinct Places #49
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: Subatomic Compositions #178
metadata.description:
My love of physics predates my love for generative systems. This piece explores the compositional beauty that can arise from particle collisions in the subatomic space. The aesthetic is based on bubble chamber photography: the paths of particles are traced and photographed as they split and collide.

The primary particle travels at extreme speeds, looping around until it collides with another particle. The resulting explosion is traced out and interesting events are highlighted. Some of the particles shoot off at incredible velocity, and others spiral tighter and tighter until they blink out of existence.

This is a study in composition.

metadata.name: Three dead trees on earth #171
metadata.description:
"Three dead trees on earth" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel.
This cycle is totally linked to my activity as a scientific researcher. Trees are data structures very much used in computer science and I worked on the random generation of these structures. It seemed interesting to me to make a link between the digital world (and these trees) and nature in danger. The 3 dead trees refer to the old beliefs of the south of France, while questioning us on the mutations of the world, and the risk to neglect our planet. Are the trees of the computer science the dead trees of our forests? To complete my work, I added a red sun, which is in fact a zonotopal subdivision (a complex mathematical object), that is to say a kind of tiling with rhombuses. I wanted to give a Japanese touch to my work, I love the minimalist poetry of Japanese gardens where everything is in its place and in harmony. Here, a desire to pay tribute to the work of Hiroshige.

metadata.name: Primordial #193
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.description:
Random is the most basic and essential tool in generative art. Yet with many different parameters, beautiful works could still be achievable with only random numbers.

This project is associated with a generative art course at NCCU in Taiwan.

metadata.name: Sideral Wind #24
metadata.description:
"Sideral" is archaic for "sidereal" and it means: emanating from the stars and especially from stars held to be malefic. Sideral Wind is an interstellar force that comes from evil celestial worlds and that can take the form of strong thunderstorms hitting and sweeping any planet in its way or generating alien bodies in the sky.

- hit 's' and save the svg file at the current resolution of display
- hit 'p' and save the png file at 3072px x 3072px
